        <div align="justify" class="txt">
            <b class="sh">New Wing Rooms - </b>These rooms offer breathtaking views of the waterfront
            and Chinese fishing nets or spectacular views of the harbor. Corner rooms offer
            views of the waterfront, harbor and of the sunset.<br />
            <br />
            <b class="sh">Heritage Wing Rooms - </b>Rooms with a Victorian touch, overlooking
            the waterfront or lush gardens.<br />
            <br />
            <b class="sh">Suites - </b><strong>Choose from 7 Executive Suites and 2 Deluxe Suites.
                Suites in the New Wing have balconies with splendid waterfront views, while those
                in the Old Wing are decorated using Indian and Chinese th</strong>emes.<br />
            <br />
            <br />
            <b>Dining :</b><br />
            <img border="0" height="1" hspace="0" src="http://www.kerala-tourism.net/gifs1/bdline.gif"
                vspace="2" width="243" /><br />
            <b class="sh">Waterfront Café - </b>The waterfront café is a 24-hour coffee shop,
            romantically situated on the Waterfront, offering you a wide range of Indian, Continental
            and Local cuisine.
            <br />
            <br />
            <b class="sh">Thai Pavilion - </b>The restaurant is the first of its kind in Kerala
            to serve authentic Thai cuisine.
            <br />
            <br />
            <b class="sh">Rice Boat - </b>A Unique restaurant set in a Rice Boat, serving ethnic
            seafood delicacies. Guests can interact with the chef, watch the ships go by and
            be serenaded by the sound of waves lapping the boat.
            <br />
            <br />
            <b class="sh">Dolphin's Point - </b>An open-air seasonal eatery serving barbequed
            delicacies cooked to your taste. It is open on Fridays, Saturdays and Sundays.
            <br />
            <br />
            <b class="sh">Mattancherry - </b>The Lobby Lounge bar set in a Colonial ambience.
            The bar serves spirits and cocktails as well as an assortment of ethnic Keralite,
            Thai &amp; International snacks. A pianist plays light music in the evenings.
            <br />
            <br />
            <b class="sh">Pool Side Bar - </b>An enchanting bar, overlooking Aquarius, the swimming
            pool. The bar serves a wide range of exotic cocktails and mocktails and snacks,
            throughout the day.
            <br />
            <br />
            Multi-cuisine restaurant serves Indian, Continental and Chinese cuisine and seafood
            specialties. Specialty restaurant serves delicacies of the west coast. Coffee shop
            with snacks, pastries and ice creams
            <br />
            <br />
            <br />
            <b>Conference and Banquet facilities :</b><br />
            <img border="0" height="1" hspace="0" src="http://www.kerala-tourism.net/gifs1/bdline.gif"
                vspace="2" width="243" /><br />
            Sit council like the Maharajah did. Hold a conference at the Raja Varma, Bristow
            or the Willingdon Hall. Furnished with the best of modern business facilities, they
            can comfortably accommodate 70 to 300 people. The hotel also has a state-of-the-art
            business centre with 2 small meeting/board-rooms.<br />
            <br />
            Round off a successful conference with a theme evening organized on our lawns and
            you'll feel all the tension slowly ebbing away. Rejoice in the art of Mohiniattam,
            one of India's most graceful dance forms. Or gaze in awe at the colorful vibrancy
            of Kathakali, dance drama. Under a star studded night sky and gently swaying palms.<br />
